{"annotations": [{"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "chromosomes", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.8241183757781982, "span": {"begin": 45, "end": 56}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "homologous chromosomes", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.8427996635437012, "span": {"begin": 228, "end": 250}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "daughter", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.5282994508743286, "span": {"begin": 318, "end": 326}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "daughter cell", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8415888547897339, "span": {"begin": 318, "end": 331}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "chromosome", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.7449291348457336, "span": {"begin": 364, "end": 374}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "chromatids", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.5893117189407349, "span": {"begin": 392, "end": 402}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SAC", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.6536001563072205, "span": {"begin": 450, "end": 453}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "misaligned chromosomes", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.7077479362487793, "span": {"begin": 550, "end": 572}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "oocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8327312469482422, "span": {"begin": 597, "end": 604}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SAC", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.5660761594772339, "span": {"begin": 610, "end": 613}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "misaligned chromosomes", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.5093352794647217, "span": {"begin": 682, "end": 704}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "KER", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.6882399320602417, "span": {"begin": 715, "end": 718}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SAC", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.7749485373497009, "span": {"begin": 817, "end": 820}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "aneuploid cell", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.8858920335769653, "span": {"begin": 878, "end": 892}}], "text": "Chromosome dynamics refers to the ability of chromosomes to congress at the metaphase plate before segregation and attach in an amphitelic orientation [Mailhes and Marchetti, 2010]. Amphitelic refers to the proper attachment of homologous chromosomes to a bipolar spindle and their orientation to opposite poles. Each daughter cell is then expected to receive one chromosome (composed of two chromatids), resulting in a haploid state. Cells have the SAC that monitors chromosome dynamics and should prevent anaphase from occurring in the presence of misaligned chromosomes, however, especially in oocytes, the SAC is not always able to arrest meiotic progression in the presence of misaligned chromosomes.  In this KER, alterations in chromosome dynamics lead to incorrect congression and alignment. In addition, the SAC fails to prevent chromosome segregation, resulting in an aneuploid cell.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:48:26 +0000 2026"}